Obituaries

















Clarence H. Smith 

(April 28, 1949 - August 14, 2008)



Guest Book
 | 
Sign Guest Book



Clarence H. “Smitty” Smith, 59, of Naples, died Thursday, August 14, 2008 at the Charles George V.A. Medical Center in Asheville after bravely fighting cancer for the last several years. He was dearly loved and will be sorely missed. 
A native of Buncombe County, Smitty was born in Asheville on April 28, 1949, a son of the late Dennis Lee and Evelyn Smith, both of Asheville. He was also preceded in death by his brother, Bill Lee Smith and sisters, Jeannette Brockmeyer and Judy Smith. 
He was an honored member of the United States Marine Corps and proudly served his country in the Vietnam War. Smitty was also a loyal employee of Blue Ridge Metals. 
Smitty is survived by his devoted wife, Tammy; loving son, Scott Smith and his wife, Amy, of Bryson City; step-son, Jeremiah Branks and companion, Meredith Aabye, of Naples; four loving sisters, Barbara, Joyce, Marie and Doris; a brother, Richard and numerous nieces, nephews and many friends. 
His family extends a special appreciation to everyone at Blue Ridge Metals for all their support and love through it all. A special thanks to the Doctors and Nursing Staff at the V.A. Hospital for the loving care they provided in his time of need. The family would also like to thank everyone for their thoughts and prayers. 
A memorial service will be held at 2:00p.m., Sunday, August 17, 2008 at Shepherd’s Church Street Chapel with Mr. Billy Dale Ecklund Smith officiating. Military Rites will be conducted by: Hubert M. Smith American Legion Post #77 Hedrick-Rhodes VFW Post #5206 Chapter #14 of the DAV. The family will receive friends 4:00-6:00p.m., Saturday at the home of his sister, Barbara Redmond. 









